
Prerequisites for EasyOCaml are the same like for OCaml (see INSTALL)

Steps:

 $ ./configure [-prefix <path/to/install/dir>]
 $ ./build/smallworld.sh
 $ ./build/install.sh

Optional:
 Build the HTML error reporter:
   $ boot/ocamlrun boot/myocamlbuild -tag-line 'true: -use_stdlib' easyadd/htmlErrorReport.cmo
 Use not with ecaml but with ecamlc
   $ ecamlc -easyerrorprinter _build/easyadd/htmlErrorReport.cmo

